snippet.textDisplay: My dad has a black '96 with very low miles and there is this feature that it has to were you can strait pipe it with a switch under the car under the center consul.  I'd check and see if yours has it too. If you do, then that would be the reason for the only 2 inside exhaust pipes smoking. The other 2 (outside 2) are for the strait pipe. Just a theory, not fact. Also, I love the 80-90 vetts.
